# According to Evert Vorster
# MesaLib should be compiled with -fno-strict-aliasing added to CFLAGS
# in order for OpenGL to work with xf86-video-intel drivers

with info    last 20130826
with version   stable 2.21.15 2.21.14 2.21.13
with base    libXvMC xcb-util xorg-server
with also    --disable-static
with role    xorg/driver
with trait   x11 X11R7 library makej multilib-concurrent optimize
with source    stable $XORG_URL driver/$SPELL-$VERSION.tar.bz2
with source  unstable $XORG_URL driver/$SPELL-$VERSION.tar.bz2
with info    home http://www.x.org/
